(song fading away)

14:54.327 --> 14:57.330
Oh, those were
good times.

14:57.397 --> 15:00.533
Hey, buddy, you remember
that time you shaved my...

15:00.600 --> 15:01.601
Please just stop talking.

15:01.668 --> 15:03.370
DOCTOR:
All right.

15:03.436 --> 15:06.373
Let's sever some vas deferens.

15:06.439 --> 15:07.407
Hey, Jimmy.

15:07.474 --> 15:08.441
Yeah?

15:08.508 --> 15:10.010
Pull my finger.

15:10.077 --> 15:10.978
I really don't think so.

15:11.044 --> 15:12.779
Come on, buddy.
No.

15:12.845 --> 15:15.382
I don't want to-- I had
to drag you in from the car,

15:15.448 --> 15:17.084
I had to hold you
down on the bed,

15:17.150 --> 15:18.151
I had to shave you

15:18.218 --> 15:19.919
below your waist.
I am not lifting,

15:19.987 --> 15:23.656
moving, tugging or pulling
anything else of yours today.

15:23.723 --> 15:26.559
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna go to the bathroom

15:26.626 --> 15:27.827
and wash my eyes.

15:27.894 --> 15:30.030
(sighs)

15:32.532 --> 15:34.434
(door slams)

15:54.687 --> 15:57.124
(whispering):
We have another problem.

15:59.192 --> 16:01.261
Last night, we were having
a normal dinner:

16:01.328 --> 16:03.296
fish for Friday.

16:03.363 --> 16:05.365
For the first time in days,

16:05.432 --> 16:07.434
I actually forgot
about your situation.

16:07.500 --> 16:10.637
I could feel calm--
but I was too calm.

16:10.703 --> 16:13.606
So, anything interesting
happen to anyone today?

16:13.673 --> 16:14.974
Any gossip?

16:16.809 --> 16:17.877
He said "gossip"?

16:17.944 --> 16:18.911
Yes!
No.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.780
Yes!
God!
I know.

16:20.847 --> 16:22.249
Soon as I heard that,

16:22.315 --> 16:24.551
the gossip started
to fight its way out.

16:24.617 --> 16:27.154
I saw some pretty cool out-
of-state license plates today.

16:27.220 --> 16:28.355
(mouth full):
Do tell.

16:28.421 --> 16:29.822
Well, I saw this Alaskan one.

16:29.889 --> 16:31.424
I felt like I had an armadillo

16:31.491 --> 16:34.127
inside me trying
to claw its way out.

16:34.194 --> 16:36.029
I looked away,
and I kept telling myself...

16:36.096 --> 16:37.397
(whispers):
Sex tape. Sex tape.

16:37.464 --> 16:39.132
But then Hope
threw a curveball,

16:39.199 --> 16:40.900
and I was back
to thinking "baby."

16:40.967 --> 16:43.336
I just lost it!

16:44.537 --> 16:46.005
Oh, look.

16:46.073 --> 16:47.340
Look...

16:47.407 --> 16:48.575
she's got something.

16:48.641 --> 16:50.177
BURT:
Mama's got
a secret.
Mm-mm.

16:50.243 --> 16:51.878
No, I don't.

16:51.944 --> 16:53.012
Yes, you do.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.814
Come on, spill
it, spill it.

16:54.881 --> 16:56.349
JIMMY/BURT:
Spill it, spill it, spill it.

16:56.416 --> 16:57.317
JIMMY:
Just let it out...

16:57.384 --> 16:59.552
I lost our sex tape!

16:59.619 --> 17:02.355
You told your own secret?
I had to.

17:02.422 --> 17:05.425
They knew I had gossip,
and they weren't gonna stop
until I told them something.

17:05.492 --> 17:07.994
And the only other secret
I could think of other
than yours was mine.

17:08.061 --> 17:09.329
What was Burt's reaction?

17:09.396 --> 17:11.198
Not what I expected.

17:12.699 --> 17:13.833
(laughing)

17:13.900 --> 17:16.269
Somebody's sitting down
to watch Vin Diesel,

17:16.336 --> 17:18.338
and they're gonna see my wiener!

17:18.405 --> 17:20.507
(continues
laughing)

17:20.573 --> 17:23.576
'Cause it looks a little
like Vin Diesel. (laughing)

17:23.643 --> 17:25.845
So, what happened
with my secret?

17:25.912 --> 17:28.415
Nothing. I just bit my tongue
for the rest of the night.

17:28.481 --> 17:30.217
Look, it's still
bleeding a little.

17:30.283 --> 17:31.751
(disgusted groan)
But I can't

17:31.818 --> 17:34.187
do that every day, so, listen,
if you're really pregnant,

17:34.254 --> 17:35.622
we're just gonna have to agree

17:35.688 --> 17:37.424
to tell people sooner
rather than later.

17:37.490 --> 17:40.127
Well... I've been
putting this off,

17:40.193 --> 17:42.129
but... I guess it's time.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.164
Let's go.

17:45.632 --> 17:46.866
(pounding on door)

17:46.933 --> 17:49.769
Someone's in here.

17:53.140 --> 17:54.207
Sabrina, hurry.

17:54.274 --> 17:55.675
They were giving out
coffee samples

17:55.742 --> 17:59.146
in the store, and there's a line
of cheap, jittery women outside.

18:00.413 --> 18:02.215
(exhales)
I don't have a baby!

18:02.282 --> 18:04.317
And I don't have a secret!

18:09.756 --> 18:11.224
Oh, hey, Tyler.

18:11.291 --> 18:13.360
You work here,
too, huh?
Oh, yeah.

18:13.426 --> 18:15.995
Between the propane and
the wind and the solar,

18:16.062 --> 18:17.464
who knows how long

18:17.530 --> 18:19.566
natural gas is
gonna be around for.

18:19.632 --> 18:22.535
But Pac-Man, that's forever.

18:23.803 --> 18:25.738
You looking
for your pops.
Yeah.

18:25.805 --> 18:27.207
Photo booth.

18:30.510 --> 18:32.078
Dad, I know
you're in there.

18:32.145 --> 18:33.980
Just come on out.
No!

18:34.046 --> 18:36.649
If he's not gonna come out,
he's got to take some pictures.

18:45.192 --> 18:48.295
I know you're afraid about
going through with this, Dad.

18:48.361 --> 18:50.830
I'm not afraid.
After the pill
that guy gave me,

18:50.897 --> 18:53.666
you could've examined
my prostate, I wouldn't
even have flinched.

18:53.733 --> 18:54.867
He did.

18:54.934 --> 18:56.002
See?

18:56.068 --> 18:58.070
(beeping)

18:58.137 --> 18:59.506
(flashbulb pops, shutter clicks)

18:59.572 --> 19:01.208
Then why did you run?

19:01.274 --> 19:02.775
Because you refused
to pull my finger.

19:02.842 --> 19:06.813
But, Dad, it was
a long, hard day.

19:06.879 --> 19:08.648
I just wasn't in the mood
for goofing around.

19:08.715 --> 19:10.250
I'm worried about us
growing apart.

19:10.317 --> 19:11.818
I know you'll
always be my son,

19:11.884 --> 19:13.953
but I don't know
you'll always be my buddy.

19:14.020 --> 19:15.822
What?

19:15.888 --> 19:19.392
Look... I know I'm
like Mad magazine--

19:19.459 --> 19:22.061
my audience is
a pretty specific age,

19:22.128 --> 19:24.397
probably, like, ten to 17.

19:24.464 --> 19:26.766
You're 22 now--
you got a kid
of your own.

19:26.833 --> 19:29.336
You might be outgrowing
the Burt Show.

19:29.402 --> 19:32.572
Having you was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

19:32.639 --> 19:35.308
But if you outgrew me,
I'd like to have the option

19:35.375 --> 19:37.043
to make another little buddy.

19:37.109 --> 19:39.312
(beeping)

19:39.379 --> 19:41.180
(flashbulb pops, shutter clicks)

19:41.248 --> 19:44.984
Wait. Having me was
the best thing that
ever happened to you?

19:45.051 --> 19:46.686
Greatest day of my life.

19:46.753 --> 19:49.222
Well, I always figured
that since I was a mistake,

19:49.289 --> 19:52.292
you guys would rather I turned
out to be a pregnancy scare.

19:52.359 --> 19:54.427
Of course not.

19:54.494 --> 19:56.763
I will always be your buddy.

19:56.829 --> 19:58.231
And I promise

19:58.298 --> 20:01.568
I will never get tired
of the Burt Show.

20:02.935 --> 20:05.272
I'm not a machine, Jimmy.

20:05.338 --> 20:07.106
I need a little time to...

20:07.173 --> 20:08.341
Hold it. Wait.

20:08.408 --> 20:10.410
(beeping)
Okay, now!

20:16.048 --> 20:18.785
JIMMY:
When Dad realized that
he truly had a buddy for life,

20:18.851 --> 20:20.487
he happily went through
with the vasectomy.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.955
Time to switch.
These are still
pretty cold.

20:23.022 --> 20:26.493
Yeah, but Mom needs the peas
for the shepherd's pie.

20:28.328 --> 20:29.829
(chuckles)

20:29.896 --> 20:31.030
Berries.

20:31.097 --> 20:32.665
He wasn't the only one
who learned

20:32.732 --> 20:35.034
that having a buddy
you can trust is a cool thing.

20:35.101 --> 20:37.504
Now that you know about my
summer at sleep away camp,

20:37.570 --> 20:39.372
now you got to tell me
something about you.

20:39.439 --> 20:44.277
Oh. Remember that time
somebody knocked over the
statue at the black church,

20:44.344 --> 20:47.079
everybody thought
it was a hate crime?

20:47.146 --> 20:51.284
That was the day I taught myself
how to drive a stick shift.

20:51.351 --> 20:53.152
(laughing)

20:53.219 --> 20:54.487
I learned something, too.

20:54.554 --> 20:56.623
Even though I was a mistake,

20:56.689 --> 20:59.859
I'm a mistake my parents
would gladly make again.

21:04.030 --> 21:08.901
And that is something you and I
definitely have in common.

21:08.968 --> 21:12.238
I couldn't have planned how you
came to me in a million years.

21:12.305 --> 21:13.773
But I always want
you to know,

21:13.840 --> 21:15.875
you're the best thing
that ever happened to me.

21:15.942 --> 21:18.911
Which is why I'm going to teach
you a Chance family tradition.

21:18.978 --> 21:21.013
Pull my finger.

21:21.080 --> 21:22.281
Come on.

21:22.349 --> 21:24.016
Pull it.

21:24.083 --> 21:25.752
Here.

21:25.818 --> 21:27.920
Like this.

21:27.987 --> 21:29.722
(quiet flatulence)

21:29.789 --> 21:32.392
(laughing)

21:35.061 --> 21:37.029
CHILD: Bi... ble. The end.
